People ex rel. Cecilia Van Norman v. The Central Car and Manufacturing Company. Mandamus to private corporation to pay dividends. Submitted June 10. George W. Moore for the motion.

Mandamus is not a proper remedy to compel a private corporation to pay dividends which it has declared; still less when any other question exists as to the rights of the, person claiming to be entitled to them.

*167Motion for order to show cause.

Denied June 11.
